<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Furman 16, Elon 3  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GREENVILLE, S.C. (AP) -- Freshman Danny Marshall hit three field
goals and tailback Louis Ivory ran for 182 yards as Furman defeated
Elon 16-3 on Saturday night in the opening game for both teams.
</P>
<P>
   The Paladins, who shared the Southern Conference championship a
year ago, fell to Elon in the opener here a year ago. The Phoenix
looked like they might pull off another one as they trailed 9-3 and
were driving late in the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
   But Furman safety Shelvis Smith recovered a fumble by Elon
quarterback Derrick Moore at the Paladin 10-yard line.
</P>
<P>
   Ivory put the game away a play later with a 75-yard TD run.
</P>
<P>
   Elon outgained Furman 325 to 236, but gave up four fumbles and
two interceptions.
</P>
<P>
   Marshall hit field goals of 43, 29 and 34 yards as the Paladins
took a 9-0 lead with 13:45 in the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Elon's only score was a 27-yard field goal by Beau Wegmann with
6:40 to go in the third period.
</P>
<P>
   The Phoenix had their chances, but did not score on their final
five possessions. Four of those ended inside Furman territory.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
