<HEADLINE> Willie Nelson Plays the Blues  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Country music today is giving Willie Nelson
the blues.
</P>
<P>
   And he's giving them back, in concerts and on an upcoming CD.
</P>
<P>
   Most audiences have tired of hearing the pop music that
dominates most country radio stations, said Nelson, 67.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think they decided to go off in a different direction, to go
more rock 'n' roll,'' he told the L.A. Times on Saturday. ''And
they wound up with a melted-down version of something else. It's
not country, it's not rock 'n' roll.''
</P>
<P>
   Nelson, who has been performing blues songs regularly at his
concerts, will be releasing a blues collection, ''Milk Cow Blues,''
on Sept. 19. It features collaborations with blues veterans such as
B.B. King, Dr. John, Keb' Mo' and Jimmie Vaughan.
</P>
