<HEADLINE> Bodies of 3 Workers Found in Grozny  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NAZRAN, Russia (AP) -- Russian troops in the Chechen capital
Grozny found the bodies of three emergency workers who had
apparently been shot and stabbed to death, a news report said
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The three Emergency Situations Ministry workers were found with
multiple gunshot and stabbing wounds in Grozny's Zavodskoi
district, the Interfax news agency said. The ministry handles civil
disasters and has a large compound in Grozny containing sleeping
quarters for dozens of staff and a field hospital.
</P>
<P>
   A ministry duty officer refused to comment on the report.
</P>
<P>
   The three workers were related to each other, Interfax said
without identifying them.
</P>
<P>
   Russian troops captured Grozny in early February after weeks of
air and artillery strikes, but have been unable to keep rebels from
filtering back into the city. Federal forces occupy about two
thirds of the republic.
</P>
<P>
   A Russian soldier was wounded Sunday near the city of Argun when
the convoy he was riding in came under fire, the news agency
ITAR-Tass reported.
</P>
<P>
   Also Sunday, Russian forces said they expected rebels to launch
a new operation around Sept. 6, when the insurgents celebrate the
1996 anniversary of the day they ousted Russian troops from
Chechnya at the end of a 1994-96 war.
</P>
<P>
   The federal command's press center said rebels would provoke
federal troops into bombing peaceful towns and try to assassinate
several pro-Russian Chechen officials in the republic.
</P>
<P>
   Russian forces have repeatedly warned that rebels were planning
attacks around holidays or events in Russia, but there have been no
major rebel attacks in weeks.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
