<HEADLINE> Suspicious fire claims one life, injures six  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP)- A suspicious fire that started early Sunday
morning in the Bedford-Stuyvesant section of Brooklyn claimed a
teen-ager's life and injured six other people, fire officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The fire began shortly before 7 a.m. in a three-story
residential building with a business on the first floor and was
burning full force when firefighters arrived minutes later, said
Firefighter Robert Calise.
</P>
<P>
   One resident, Armony Bevel, 18, was declared dead at the scene
and two others, a woman in her 60s and a 34-year-old man, were
injured, the woman in critical condition with burns and the man in
stable condition, said Detective John Giammarino, a police
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   Four firefighters were brought to Kings County Medical Center
with injuries and were all in stable condition, Calise said.
</P>
<P>
   The fire was deemed suspicious and was under investigation
because of its heavy volume and the speed with which it spread,
Calise said.
</P>
</TEXT>
