<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-03 19:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Ties Hungary in World Cup  </HEADLINE>
By STEPHEN WADE
<TEXT>
<P>
   Ferenc Horvath scored his second goal of the game in the 79th
minute as Hungary rallied to tie Italy 2-2 on Sunday in Budapest in
a 2002 World Cup qualifier.
</P>
<P>
   Filippo Inzaghi scored for Italy in the 26th and 35th minutes,
and Horvath got his first in the 29th in the Group 8 match. It was
Italy's first game since losing the Euro 2000 final to France.
</P>
<P>
   In Sunday's other European qualifiers, it was the Faeroe Islands
2, Slovenia 2; Luxembourg 0, Yugoslavia 2; Estonia 1, Portugal 3;
Slovakia 2, Macedonia 0; Israel 2, Lichtenstein 0; and Romania 1,
Lithuania 0.
</P>
<P>
   In North and Central America and Caribbean play, it was the
United States 1, Guatemala 0; Costa Rica 3, Barbados 0; Mexico 7,
Panama 1; Trinidad and Tobago 4, Canada 0. Jamaica faced St.
Vincent and the Grenadines in a night game.
</P>
<P>
   In South America, it Brazil 5, Bolivia 0; and Uruguay 4, Ecuador
0. Argentina faced Peru in a late game.
</P>
<P>
Europe
Group 1
</P>
<P>
   At Torshavn, Faeroe Islands, the Atlantic islanders tied
Slovenia 2-2 with Oessur Hansen scoring the equalizer in injury
time. Uni Arge also scored for the Faeroe Islands. Saso Udovic and
Milan Osterc scored for Slovenia.
</P>
<P>
   At Luxembourg, Yugoslavia beat Luxembourg 2-0 on goals by Savo
Milosevic and Slavisa Jokanovic. Yugoslavia, under new coach Ilija
Petkovic, shares the early group lead with Russia.
</P>
<P>
Group 2
</P>
<P>
   At Tallinn, Estonia, Manuel Rui Costa, Luis Figo and Ricardo Sa
Pinto scored in the first 54 minutes as Portugal beat Estonia 3-1.
Andres Oper scored in the 84th for Estonia.
</P>
<P>
Group 4
</P>
<P>
   At Bratislava, Slovakia, Igor Balis scored in the third minute
and Igor Demo added the second in the 74th as Slovakia beat
Macedonia 2-0.
</P>
<P>
Group 7
</P>
<P>
   At Ramat Gan, Israel, Alon Mizrahi scored after just 16 seconds
and Pini Balili got the other in the 79th in Israel's 2-0 victory
over Lichtenstein.
</P>
<P>
Group 8
</P>
<P>
   At Bucharest, Romania, Ioan Ganea scored in the 89th minute as
Romania beat Lithuania 1-0 in the opening qualifier for each side.
</P>
<P>
North, Central America, Caribbean
Group E
</P>
<P>
   At Washington, Brian McBride scored off a perfect cross from
Cobi Jones in the 72nd minute and the United States, playing a man
short, escaped with a 1-0 victory over Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
   The Americans, desperately needing a win to avoid putting
themselves in must-win situations for their final two games, were
rocked in the 65th minute. Eddie Lewis, who had entered seven
minutes earlier, was ejected by Mexican referee Ulises Rangel for
elbowing Fabricio Benitez.
</P>
<P>
   At San Jose, Costa Rica, the Costa Ricans beat Barbados 3-0 on
goals by Jafet Soto, Rolando Fonseca and Hernan Medford.
</P>
<P>
Group C
</P>
<P>
   At Mexico City, Mexico advanced to the final qualifying round
with a 7-1 victory Panama. Cuauhtemoc Blanco scored twice.
</P>
<P>
   At Port-of-Spain, Trinidad, Canada fell out of World Cup
contention with a 4-0 loss to Trinidad and Tobago. Russell Latapy,
Reynold Carrington, Stokely Mason and Angus Eve scored.
</P>
<P>
South America
</P>
<P>
   At Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, Romario scored three goals in his
comeback to international play as Brazil beat Bolivia 5-0. He had
not played in an international game since a 1998 friendly against
Argentina. Rivaldo and Marques also scored.
</P>
<P>
   At Montevideo, Uruguay, Federico Magallanes had a goal and an
assist in Uruguay's 4-0 victory over Ecuador.
</P>
</TEXT>
