<HEADLINE> Blast at Car Dealership in Athens  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATHENS, Greece (AP) -- An explosion at a British car dealership
here on Sunday caused minor damages and no injuries, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The late night blast at a Jaguar dealership in the Rendi
district of the capital damaged the facade of the building. Police,
who said the blast may have been caused by a time bomb, cordoned
off the building while a bomb squad searched the area.
</P>
<P>
   There was no immediate claim of responsibility for the blast.
</P>
<P>
   Terrorist groups and arson gangs carry out numerous attacks each
year, usually targeting the cars and offices of Athens government
agencies, large companies, diplomatic missions and journalists.
Nearly 100 arson attacks have been carried out so far this year.
</P>
