<HEADLINE> Man charged with murdering ex-girlfriend, stabbing her boyfriend  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   FLORHAM PARK, N.J. (AP) - A Berkeley Heights man has been
charged with murdering his ex-girlfriend and stabbing her boyfriend
after the couple returned from a wedding early Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
   Vincent P. Conte, 48, has been charged with the murder of
Deborah Schroeder, 45, according to Morris County Prosecutor John
B. Dangler. Conte is also charged with aggravated assault and
possession of a weapon, Dangler said.
</P>
<P>
   Schroeder and her boyfriend, Joseph DeMayo, 41, of Harrison,
were attacked in the bedroom of her home at about 2 a.m. with a
knife and baseball bat. Dangler said Conte entered the bedroom and
began stabbing the couple and also hit both in the head with the
bat.
</P>
<P>
   DeMayo ran to a neighbor's house and police were notified. When
police arrived they found Schroeder dead. Conte had self-inflicted
stab wounds, Dangler said. DeMayo was treated for stab wounds to
his forearms and hands and a head injury.
</P>
<P>
   Conte's eight-year relationship with Schroeder had ended
recently, Dangler said.
</P>
<P>
   Bail for Conte was set at $750,000 and he is under police guard
at Morristown Memorial Hospital, Dangler said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
