<HEADLINE> Suspicious NYC Fire Kills 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- A fire broke out in a residential building early
Sunday, killing two people and injuring five others, including four
firefighters, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Two residents, an 18-year-old man and a woman in her 60s, were
killed, and a 34-year-old man was injured in the Brooklyn fire. He
was in stable condition, said Detective John Giammarino, a police
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   The firefighters were released later Sunday after being treated
for exhaustion and smoke inhalation.
</P>
<P>
   Firefighter Robert Calise said said authorities consider the
fire suspicious and still were investigating.
</P>
