<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-03 22:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suspicious fire claims two lives, injures five  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - A suspicious fire that started early Sunday
morning in the Bedford-Stuyvesant section of Brooklyn killed two
people, including a teen-ager, and injured five others, fire
officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The fire began shortly before 7 a.m. in a three-story
residential building with a business on the first floor and was
burning full force when firefighters arrived minutes later, said
Firefighter Robert Calise.
</P>
<P>
   One resident, Armony Bevel, 18, was declared dead at the scene,
and an unidentified woman in her 60s died later at St. John's
Hospital. A 34-year-old man was injured and was in stable
condition, said Detective John Giammarino, a police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   Four firefighters were treated for injuries at Kings County
Medical Center and released, Calise said.
</P>
<P>
   The fire was deemed suspicious and was under investigation
because of its heavy volume and the speed with which it spread,
Calise said.
</P>
</TEXT>
