<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Morse Wins Utah Classic  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SANDY, Utah (AP) -- Andrew Morse won his first Buy.com Tour title
Sunday, closing with a 4-under-par 68 for a two-stroke victory over
John Riegger in the Utah Classic.
</P>
<P>
   Morse, 41, played 32 holes Sunday in the rain-plagued
tournament. After opening with rounds of 64 and 66, he shot a 71
Sunday morning en route to a 19-under 269 total.
</P>
<P>
   ''Basically, my career has been one stroke short,'' Morse said.
''Whether it be for a tournament or qualifying or the PGA Tour
school. But paying enough dues has finally come on the other side
of it. I'm two strokes ahead this time.''
</P>
<P>
   Morse earned $72,000 to jump from 59th to 18th on the money list
with $131,353. The top 15 at the end of the season will earn 2001
PGA Tour cards.
</P>
<P>
   Riegger shot a 67 on the Willow Creek course. Bo Van Pelt closed
with a 69 to finish third at 272.
</P>
</TEXT>
