<BODY>
<HEADLINE> El Corredor Wins Del Mar  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- El Corredor beat Cliquot by 2&AMP;frac12; lengths
Sunday in the $250,600 Del Mar Breeders' Cup Handicap.
</P>
<P>
   El Corredor, ridden by Victor Espinoza, ran a mile over the fast
track in 1:35. The 3-year-old colt paid $7.20, $3.80 and $3.20 for
his fourth victory in five starts.
</P>
<P>
   The winner earned $158,600 to raise his career earnings to
$267,920. As a yearling, he was bought for $110,000 and has seldom
raced due to physical ailments. He won a claiming race last month,
his first start since January.
</P>
<P>
   Cliquot, ridden by Kent Desormeaux, returned $3.80 and $3.20,
and Literal Prowler paid $4.20 to show.
</P>
<P>
   Espinoza also guided Lazy Slusan to a two-length victory in the
$136,200 Solana Beach Handicap. Lazy Slusan ran a mile on the turf
course in 1:34 1-5, and paid $10.20, $3.40 and $2.60.
</P>
</TEXT>
