inspired but drained and cramping Max Mirnyi.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Dodgers Beat Phillies 6-1
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Chan Ho Park won his fourth consecutive start, allowing
two hits over eight innings as the Los Angeles Dodgers completed a three-game
sweep of the Philadelphia Phillies with a 6-1 victory Sunday night. The
Phillies' only hits off Park (15-8) were Scott Rolen's two-out single in the
first inning and Tomas Perez's leadoff single in the eighth. The right-hander
struck out six, tied a season high with seven walks and induced three
double-play grounders, while matching his career high in victories.
AP NewsBrief by MARIA CODER 
</P>
